issue.title: IronPython Build Issues
issue.body: IronPython does not seem to be compatible with Unity's compilation system. As a result the python code execution only appears to work in the editor. Not sure how to work around this.

issue.title: Coding Challenges Fail
issue.body: Any input on a coding challenge appears to open the door. The debug log is showing correct execution of the program however. Might have something to do with how the response is being sent back? Any ideas on how to fix?

issue.title: Unnecessary scene jump for questions.
issue.body: Unnecessary scene jump to enter or leave a question. This can be eliminated using prefabrification. The scene jump introduces all kinds of variables and issues, such as a need for an entry point, global vars and door management.
